---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import CTABand from '../components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Bundle is building the aggregation layer for private markets — every crowdfunding round, secondary block and pre-IPO offer on one screen. Founded by Arjun Arun and Madhavi Bansal."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About Bundle"
    title='Private markets are having their <em class="serif-aside">Skyscanner moment.</em>'
    lead="Flights were bookable long before they were comparable. Private-market deals are exactly there today: live on a dozen venues, visible on none of them together. Bundle is the comparison layer."
  />

  <!-- Mission narrative -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose mx-auto reveal">
        <p>
          The last decade solved <strong>access</strong>: crowdfunding platforms
          let anyone back a startup, and secondary marketplaces let employees
          and early backers sell before an IPO. The next decade is solving
          <strong>liquidity</strong> — tender programmes, order-book
          marketplaces and, in the UK, the PISCES regime for regulated
          private-share trading windows.
        </p>
        <blockquote>
          What nobody solved is discovery. The market exists — it's just
          unwatchable.
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          A serious private-market investor today runs a dozen tabs: two
          crowdfunding platforms, three secondary marketplaces, a couple of
          newsletters, a spreadsheet for the portfolio. Deals close before they
          hear about them. The same company trades at different prices on
          different venues, and nobody notices. That fragmentation isn't a
          detail — it's the whole problem.
        </p>
        <p>
          Bundle aggregates the market the way Skyscanner aggregated flights:
          scan every venue, normalise every listing, put price against price —
          then route you to the venue to do the deal under its regulatory
          protections. We don't hold your money, we don't sell you our own
          inventory, and we don't reorder the market for commission. The
          aggregator only works if it's ruthlessly neutral, so that neutrality
          is the product.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founders -->
  <section class="section section-tint-full">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">The founders</p>
        <h2 class="h2 reveal" style="--d:.05s">Built at Oxford. Aimed at the gap.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid cols-2 founders-grid">
        <article class="card card-hover reveal">
          <span class="icon-chip"><Icon name="users" size={20} /></span>
          <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:1.1rem">Arjun Arun</h3>
          <p class="small muted" style="margin-bottom:0">
            Co-founder. Oxford Saïd MBA. Product and markets — obsessed with
            why private-market investors accept tooling that public-market
            investors would laugh at.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-hover reveal" style="--d:.07s">
          <span class="icon-chip"><Icon name="users" size={20} /></span>
          <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:1.1rem">Madhavi Bansal</h3>
          <p class="small muted" style="margin-bottom:0">
            Co-founder. Oxford Saïd MBA. Operations and partnerships — building
            the venue relationships and data plumbing that make one tape out of
            a fragmented market.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">Operating principles</p>
        <h2 class="h2 reveal" style="--d:.05s">Three rules we don't trade away</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <article class="card card-hover reveal">
          <span class="icon-chip"><Icon name="scale" size={20} /></span>
          <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:1.1rem">Neutral or nothing</h3>
          <p class="small muted" style="margin-bottom:0">
            Results rank by your filters, never by our commission. Sponsored
            placement, if it ever exists, gets a label you can't miss.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-hover reveal" style="--d:.07s">
          <span class="icon-chip"><Icon name="lock" size={20} /></span>
          <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:1.1rem">Never touch the money</h3>
          <p class="small muted" style="margin-bottom:0">
            Execution, custody and investor protections belong to the regulated
            venue that lists the deal. Bundle is the screen, not the till.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-hover reveal" style="--d:.14s">
          <span class="icon-chip"><Icon name="alert" size={20} /></span>
          <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:1.1rem">Honest about risk</h3>
          <p class="small muted" style="margin-bottom:0">
            Aggregation makes the market visible, not safe. Every deal on the
            tape can go to zero, and the site says so everywhere it matters.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand
    title="Help us put the whole market <em>on one screen.</em>"
    sub="Investor or venue, we'd like to hear from you."
    primaryLabel="Get early access"
    primaryHref="/waitlist"
    secondaryLabel="Contact us"
    secondaryHref="/contact"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .founders-grid {
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
</style>
